Customer Advisor, ThailandTrip.com (Thailand) Co., Ltd.Job Highlights
Solve problems for clients via call, chat, email
Inbound call center for flight and hotel products
Fluent in English, work on 24/7 shift requiredKey Roles and Responsibilities

We are seeking to build a series of high-performing teams of Customer Service Advisors to join us on our journey of growth and expansion into the Thai market. 
You will be passionate about travel, you build rapport quickly and you have a customer-centric view of the world.  These aspects will come through in all your interactions with our customers, whether on the phone, by email or by chat. 
In return we offer you a great work environment, a good benefits package and an intensive training programme to help you hit the ground running.

The standard working pattern would be 40 hours per week, over 5 days with 2 days off each week.  We will happily discuss the different shift patterns available during our selection process. 
Serve clients in Thai and English for inquiries on different Trip.com products (flight and hotel) and questions on their bookings;
Solve the problems for clients via Call, Chat and Email;
Handle clients problems with empathy and patience in a goal-driven environment;
Work as part of a high-performing team, supporting and helping colleagues when required;
Attend regular team updates;
Keep up-to-date with latest promotions and initiatives;
Read, understand and follow the Company Policies and Procedures;

Qualifications

Bachelor degree or above, or significant relevant similar experience;
Strong communication skills in Thai both verbal and written; fluent in English;
Good knowledge of Microsoft Office applications, such as Word, Excel, PowerPoint and sound general computer skills;
Proficient typing abilities with a better than average English -typing speed;
Sound troubleshooting and problem-solving skills with a strong desire to achieve positive outcomes;
Ability to listen and build rapport quickly;
Enthusiastic yet conscientious and diligent approach to work;
Completer-finisher with a good attention to detail.
Ability to touch-type;
Passionate about travel.
Able to work on a shift-based basis. 24/7 or night shift required. undefined

Assistance CoordinatorEuro-Center (Thailand) Co., Ltd.Job Highlights
Join an international team
Assist travellers worldwide
Communicate and coordinate logistic arrangementsEURO-CENTER (THAILAND) is looking for an Assistance Coordinator to join an international team of coordinators providing medical assistance to leisure and business travellers worldwide. 


Purpose of the job:

Assistance coordinator’s main task is to handle a customer service orientation and independent decision-making skills to assess and interpret the needs of the customers and to deliver efficient, cost-effective solutions to meet customer’s needs.

Main Responsibilities:


Answer incoming calls from policyholders, hospitals, agents and customers (insurance companies) on a 24/7 shift rotation basis s well as create case files;
Log in telephone call information correctly and in the right place in the internal computer;
program, in an efficient and standardized way;

Communicate with policyholder, provider or customer (insurance company) to request additional information;
Check policyholder’s details as per the first call procedure;
Assist other team members, including the claims department, as necessary, for phone call, e-mail, and case handling needing specific language expertise;
Participate in orientation programs for customers and new products;
Identify missing documents, and be able to address the relevant party to organize the missing documents;
Participate in cost containment by performing review of cases if it is required by Assistance management;
Provide summary of activities during weekly meetings;
Coordinate logistic arrangements locally and internationally to assist policyholders with medical and other claims;
Work closely with medical professionals internally and externally.
Key Qualifications:


Thai Speaking and full professional fluency in the English language will be essential for effective communication;
Fluency in a third language such as German speaking, French speaking, Spanish speaking, Scandinavian languages or Asian languages will be an advantage;
Previous work experience in medical assistance or in tourism will be an advantage;
Pro-active and performing well under pressure;
Bachelor's Degree or higher;
Good computer user skills in Microsoft Office tools;
Service-minded, positive and flexible;
Must be able to work in rotating shifts including weekends and some nights per month.
**We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified**
Interested candidates are invited to apply with a full CV/Resume (Word / PDF file), stating present and expected salary as well as a recent photograph.
Euro-Center (Thailand) Co., Ltd. • Thailand
Human Resources Department
Spring Tower Building, 22nd floor, Unit 6-10
Phayathai Road, Ratchathevi, TH - 10400 Bangkokundefined

